# Way of Pi Debian Package

## Building the .deb Package

### Requirements

To build the .deb package, you need:
- Debian/Ubuntu/Linux distribution
- `apt` package manager
- Build dependencies installed

### Build Instructions

```bash
# From the repository root
cd '/home/zerwiz/CodeP/Way of pi'

# Build the package
cd debian/source
debuild -us -uc

# This will create .deb files in debian/source/
```

### Installing from .deb

```bash
# Install the package
sudo dpkg -i ../wayof-pi_{VERSION}_amd64.deb
sudo apt-get install -f  # Fix dependencies

# Or with wget/curl from GitHub release:
wget https://github.com/zerwiz/wayofpi/releases/download/v{VERSION}/wayof-pi_{VERSION}_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i wayof-pi_{VERSION}_amd64.deb
```

## Package Structure

The package installs to:
- `/opt/wayofpi/` - The application binary and files
- `~/.local/bin/` - User scripts and aliases
- `~/.pi/` - Pi configuration directory

## Dependencies

Required system packages:
- `nodejs` (npm)
- `bun` (>= 1.3.2)
- `just`
- `build-essential`
- `dh-nodejs`

## Usage

After installation:

```bash
# Run the app
wayofpi

# Or with Electron (recommended)
./start-wayofpi-electron.sh

# Use just commands
just wayofpi-electron

# List available commands
pipx run wayofpi
```

## Configuration

### API Keys

Create `~/.pi/.env` with your API keys before first use:

```bash
cp ~/.pi/.env.sample ~/.pi/.env
# Edit ~/.pi/.env and add your keys
```

### Extensions

Extensions are located at:
- `~/.pi/agent/extensions/` - User extensions
- `~/.pi/settings.json` - Settings file

### Settings

Edit `~/.pi/settings.json` to:
- Enable/disable extensions
- Configure theme
- Set up prompt templates
- Configure agent teams

## Uninstall

```bash
sudo dpkg -r wayof-pi
# Don't forget to remove:
rm -rf ~/.pi/.wayofpi-cache ~/.pi/.wayofpi-session
```

